  + [r_hand_contact] is cycle classes and sometimes cycle-to-point or point-producing constructions
  + [phase_correction_contact] is p-adic/derived height nondegeneracy
  + [next_question] is when a nonzero derived height actually proves independent rational directions rather than only cycle-level information

& [Pair_002_ChowHeegner_PadicHeights] is a source-measurement pair
  + [source_family] is Chow-Heegner points
  + [measurement_framework] is p-adic heights and p-adic L-function values
  + [constructs_candidates] is special_setting
  + [measures_candidates] is partial
  + [independence_status] is proven_special_case_or_unknown_by_setting
  + [sufficiency_status] is special_case_only
  + [l_hand_contact] is p-adic L-function value or derivative behavior
  + [r_hand_contact] is rational points produced in selected CM or modular settings
  + [phase_correction_contact] is height nonvanishing or p-adic regulator behavior
  + [next_question] is whether Chow-Heegner constructions scale to multiple independent points or remain isolated point sources

& [Pair_003_EulerSystem_SelmerControl] is a source-measurement pair
  + [source_family] is Euler-system or Kolyvagin-system style classes
  + [measurement_framework] is Selmer-rank control and explicit reciprocity
  + [constructs_candidates] is indirect
  + [measures_candidates] is indirect
  + [independence_status] is indirect_control
  + [sufficiency_status] is not_sufficient_by_itself
  + [l_hand_contact] is reciprocity laws connecting classes to L-values or p-adic L-functions
  + [r_hand_contact] is Selmer classes rather than direct Mordell-Weil generators
  + [phase_correction_contact] is weak unless paired with height/regulator data
  + [next_question] is whether Euler-system control can certify rank bounds for source families already producing candidates

